================================================================================
C1  v1's REALISED CONNECTIVITY, redrawn from v1's own source and seeds
================================================================================
  N_exc = 8, N_inh = 2, one p_conn = 0.02 for EVERY pathway.
  Expected I->E synapses: 2 x 8 x 0.02 = 0.32

    seed   I->E synapses   TOTAL synapses
  ----------------------------------------
     100               0                1
     101               0                0
     102               0                0
     103               0                3
     104               0                0

  I->E across seeds : [0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
  TOTAL across seeds: [1, 0, 0, 3, 0]

  => Not one inhibitory-to-excitatory synapse exists on ANY seed, and
     3 of 5 seeds produced a network with zero synapses of any kind.
     v1's 'microcircuit' was ten uncoupled neurons sharing a 6 Hz drive.
     The sparsification arm removed connections from a network that had
     none. The absence of emergent gamma was uninformative, in the
     DETAILED configuration exactly as much as in the reduced ones.

================================================================================
C2  RHEOBASE OF THE HH INTERNEURON  (v1 drove it at I = 1.0)
================================================================================
  1000 ms per current. 'sustained' discards the first 200 ms, in which
  the cell fires one onset spike at EVERY current as it depolarises from
  -65 mV to the -54.4 mV leak reversal.

   I (uA/cm^2)   total  sustained   note
  ------------------------------------------------------------
           1.0       1          0   <- v1 drove the HYBRID interneurons here
           3.0       1          0   
           5.0       1          0   
           6.0       2          0   
           7.0      58         46   
          10.0      68         54   <- v1's own single-neuron block used this

  => Rheobase is between 6 and 7 uA/cm^2. At I = 1.0 the neuron
     emits 0 sustained spikes. The hybrid arm of v1 -- whose stated
     purpose was to test whether detailed inhibitory kinetics recover
     gamma -- contained interneurons that did not fire.

     v1 integrated this model with a hand-written forward Euler step;
     this is Brian2's exponential Euler at dt = 0.01 ms. Spike COUNTS
     above rheobase therefore differ by a spike or two between the two.
     The rheobase, and the silence at I = 1.0, do not.

================================================================================
M1  WHY THE PHASE-MODULATION GAMMA GENERATOR WAS DISCARDED
================================================================================
  Injecting gamma by displacing spike times with a sinusoid does not add
  a rhythm. It MULTIPLIES the 6 Hz comb by the injected frequency, and
  what appears is the intermodulation product, not the injection.

   nominal injection   peak actually found
  --------------------------------------------
               40 Hz               36.0 Hz  <- NOT the injected frequency
               55 Hz               48.0 Hz  <- NOT the injected frequency

  A positive control that does not contain the rhythm it claims to
  contain is worthless. It was replaced by ground_truth(), which is the
  UNION of two INDEPENDENT volley trains and therefore contains exactly
  the frequency it says it does.

================================================================================
M2  THE HARMONIC SCREEN'S COST DEPENDS ON THE FREQUENCY RESOLUTION
================================================================================
  The screen rejects a tolerance of +/-1.5 bins around every multiple of
  the drive, so it destroys ~3*df/f_drive of the band. At coarse
  resolution it destroys most of it -- INCLUDING any real rhythm.

    T (s)   nperseg   df (Hz)   band blocked   verdict
  --------------------------------------------------------------
      2.5      2500     0.400            20%   *** DESTROYS THE BAND ***
      3.0      3000     0.333            17%   *** DESTROYS THE BAND ***
      5.0      5000     0.200            10%   *** DESTROYS THE BAND ***
     10.0      8192     0.122             6%   usable
     21.0      8192     0.122             6%   usable

  => Requiring the blocked fraction to be at most 10% gives
     df <= 0.1 * f_drive / 3 = 0.20 Hz, i.e. a Welch segment of
     at least 5000 samples = 5.0 s. All results here use 21 s.

================================================================================
Every number in the corrigendum, and the two Methods numbers that
justified discarding v1's positive control and v1's recording length,
is produced above by code in this archive. Until this file existed they
were carried in prose, and prose does not recompute itself when the code
underneath it changes. That is not a stylistic complaint. It is the
finding of this paper, applied to this paper.
================================================================================
