##############################################################################
## artifact_demo.py
## the artifacts, on synthetic data with NO network at all
##############################################################################
====================================================================================
E1  NULL OF THE PROMINENCE STATISTIC  (constant-rate Poisson; NO rhythm)
====================================================================================
  200 independent datasets containing NO rhythm whatsoever.
  An unbiased statistic would return ~0 dB. It returns:
      mean    5.62 dB
      sd      0.61 dB
      95th    6.63 dB
      max     7.74 dB

  => Any 'gamma prominence' below ~6.6 dB is not evidence.
     v1 of this preprint reported theta prominence of 6.6-7.5 dB and
     gamma prominence of 11.3-11.9 dB against an implicit null of 0 dB.
        a reported  5.0 dB is exceeded by  88.0% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported  6.9 dB is exceeded by   3.5% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported  7.5 dB is exceeded by   1.0% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported 11.5 dB is exceeded by   0.0% of NO-rhythm data

  The null MOVES WITH THE ANALYSIS. Same data, same statistic, only
  the Welch segment length changes:

    nperseg   df (Hz)  bins in 30-80  null mean  null 95th
  ----------------------------------------------------------
       1024     0.977             51      1.48 dB     1.92 dB
       2048     0.488            102      2.31 dB     2.88 dB
       4096     0.244            204      3.60 dB     4.35 dB
       8192     0.122            409      5.58 dB     6.63 dB

  A prominence value is UNINTERPRETABLE unless the sampling rate,
  segment length and fit range are reported alongside it.

====================================================================================
E2  THETA HARMONICS MASQUERADING AS GAMMA  (6 Hz drive; gamma depth = 0)
====================================================================================
  Spike trains contain a 6 Hz modulation and NOTHING ELSE.
  Gamma-band content by construction: zero.

   depth  sharp  prom dB   null p    f_pk   k x 6Hz   null says  3 screens say
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
     0.0      1     5.33    0.686    59.3   10x6=60        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.3      1     5.66    0.646    44.8    7x6=42       17% SIG   17% rhythm
     0.6      1     5.34    0.669    41.0    7x6=42        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      1     5.76    0.377    47.9    8x6=48        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      3     5.49    0.574    65.2   11x6=66        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      6     5.53    0.537    65.1   11x6=66       17% SIG   17% rhythm
     0.9     10     7.55    0.006    30.0    5x6=30       83% SIG    0% rhythm

  => At theta depth 0.9, sharpness 10, spike trains with ZERO gamma
     produce 7.6 dB of 'gamma prominence' and the SURROGATE NULL
     calls them significant in 83% of datasets.
     The harmonic screen rejects 100% of them.

  NOTE, and it reverses a claim this file used to make: RATE MODULATION
  ALONE IS ENOUGH, if the waveform is sharp enough. These populations
  sample INDEPENDENTLY from a common rate. There is no synchrony here at
  all, and the surrogate null still calls the harmonics significant.
  Sharpening the drive concentrates its Fourier series into higher
  harmonics, and those land in the gamma band. What the surrogate cannot
  do is tell a harmonic from a rhythm, and no amount of independence in
  the spiking rescues it.

  THIS IS THE POINT: a surrogate null is NECESSARY AND NOT SUFFICIENT.
  It asks 'is there non-random fast structure?'. Theta harmonics ARE
  non-random fast structure. They are real. They are not a rhythm.

====================================================================================
E3  SCREENS CANNOT RESCUE A RHYTHM THE STATISTIC NEVER FOUND
====================================================================================
  case                        truth |  RAW: peak    verdict |  NOTCHED: peak    verdict
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  no rhythm at all            False |     61.2 Hz   rejected |         61.2 Hz   rejected
  theta-locked, sigma=5 ms    False |     30.0 Hz   rejected |         33.6 Hz   rejected
  GROUND-TRUTH 40 Hz gamma     True |     30.0 Hz rejected X |         40.0 Hz     RHYTHM
  GROUND-TRUTH 55 Hz gamma     True |     30.0 Hz rejected X |         55.1 Hz     RHYTHM

  raw statistic + four screens : WRONG on 2 of 4 cases
  notched statistic + screens  : WRONG on 0 of 4 cases

  The raw pipeline REJECTS the genuine 40 and 55 Hz rhythms. Every screen
  fires: significant, at a band edge, a harmonic of the drive. Each of
  those verdicts is CORRECT about the peak it was handed -- the peak really
  is at 30.0 Hz, and 30.0 Hz really is 5 x 6 Hz. The screens are not
  malfunctioning. They are answering a question about the wrong peak.

  A SCREEN CAN ONLY REJECT A PEAK THE STATISTIC HAS ALREADY FOUND. When the
  statistic never finds the rhythm, no number of screens can recover it,
  and adding more screens makes the pipeline more confident, not more
  correct. The comb has to come out of the SPECTRUM, before the maximum is
  taken. That is not a screen. That is a different statistic.

====================================================================================
E4  SYNCHRONY, NOT RATE, DEFEATS THE SURROGATE NULL   (gamma = 0 in every row)
====================================================================================
  6 datasets per row, N_surr = 400, T = 21 s.

   sigma |  raw dB   raw p  raw pk  raw sig |  ntch dB  ntch p  ntch sig
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    50 ms |    5.66   0.350   49.3       0% |     5.70   0.299       0%
    30 ms |    5.84   0.378   35.8      17% |     5.86   0.327      17%
    20 ms |    5.59   0.522   41.4       0% |     5.71   0.494       0%
    12 ms |   12.28   0.002   30.0     100% |     6.38   0.218      17%
     8 ms |   25.86   0.002   30.0     100% |     6.07   0.464       0%
     5 ms |   32.98   0.002   30.0     100% |     5.98   0.564       0%
     3 ms |   37.23   0.002   30.0     100% |     5.44   0.895       0%

  A null distribution is NECESSARY AND NOT SUFFICIENT. The surrogate
  asks whether there is non-random fast temporal structure. There is.
  It is the harmonics of the drive. It is entirely real. It is not gamma.

====================================================================================
E5  THE PEAK IS A HARMONIC COMB, NOT A BAND-EDGE ARTIFACT
====================================================================================
  ONE tightly-locked, gamma-free train (sigma = 5 ms). Only the band moves.

    analysis band |    peak  prominence | interpretation
  ------------------------------------------------------------------
      30-80 Hz    |   30.0      33.18 dB | = 5 x 6 Hz
      32-80 Hz    |   36.0      30.97 dB | = 6 x 6 Hz
      38-80 Hz    |   42.0      28.32 dB | = 7 x 6 Hz
      44-80 Hz    |   48.0      25.21 dB | = 8 x 6 Hz
      50-80 Hz    |   54.0      21.61 dB | = 9 x 6 Hz

  The peak does not follow the band edge. Wherever the band is placed,
  the maximum lands on a tooth of the comb.

====================================================================================
E6  THE COMB DOES NOT ONLY CREATE FALSE POSITIVES -- IT MASKS REAL RHYTHMS
====================================================================================
  Ground truth = a tight (sigma = 5 ms) 6 Hz volley train, PLUS, in three
  of four cases, a genuine independent gamma volley train.

          case |  raw dB  raw peak |  ntch dB  ntch peak | found?
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
      no gamma |   32.97     30.0 Hz |     6.03      42.6 Hz | n/a (no rhythm exists)
    real 40 Hz |   28.46     30.0 Hz |    28.91      40.0 Hz | FOUND   raw MISSED it
    real 55 Hz |   28.53     30.0 Hz |    23.55      55.1 Hz | FOUND   raw MISSED it
    real 68 Hz |   28.20     30.0 Hz |    22.21      68.0 Hz | FOUND   raw MISSED it

  The raw peak lands at 30.0 Hz in all four cases. Whether a rhythm
  exists, and at what frequency, changes its answer not at all.

====================================================================================
E7  VALIDATION OF THE REPAIR ON GROUND TRUTH
====================================================================================
  Comb-notched. N_surr = 500. 40 datasets per negative case,
  20 per positive case. A test is validated by its error rate,
  never by a single draw. Accept iff false positives <= 4/40
  (binomial, alpha = 0.05) AND power = 100%.

  case                       truth     prom       p     peak      errors  VERDICT
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  no rhythm (sigma=25 ms)     none  5.61 dB   0.538  41.1 Hz     1/40 FP  correctly rejected
  tight sigma=8, no gamma     none  6.49 dB   0.223  33.2 Hz     4/40 FP  correctly rejected
  tight sigma=3, no gamma     none  5.52 dB   0.862  39.6 Hz     1/40 FP  correctly rejected
  tight + real 40 Hz          40 Hz 29.07 dB   0.002  40.0 Hz     0/20 FN  correctly found
  tight + real 55 Hz          55 Hz 23.91 dB   0.002  55.1 Hz     0/20 FN  correctly found
  tight + real 68 Hz          68 Hz 22.68 dB   0.002  68.0 Hz     0/20 FN  correctly found

  Six of six. The false-positive rate is at nominal alpha, including
  in the worst case (3 ms locking, where the RAW statistic is wrong
  100% of the time). Power is 100%, and every rhythm is recovered to
  within 1 Hz of its true frequency.

====================================================================================
No network was simulated in this file. These are properties of the
STATISTIC and of THETA-LOCKED SPIKING, not of any one implementation.
====================================================================================
